{"type":"message","id":"578341ce","parentId":"58f66e0a","timestamp":"2026-04-03T00:37:54.256Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Hmm, it seems like the `defaults.ask: \"off\"` didn't work as expected. The exec is still being denied because there's no matching allowlist entry for this command.\n\nWait - looking at the error \"allowlist miss\", this seems different from \"approval required\". It sounds like the command itself isn't in the allowlist at all. \n\nLet me think about this... The user wanted to skip approval for main agent, but maybe the allowlist mechanism still requires the command to be in the allowlist, just without asking for approval?\n\nActually wait - looking at the first image more carefully, the `ask` setting controls whether it ASKS for approval, not whether it requires an allowlist entry. So even with `ask: \"off\"`, the command still needs to be in the allowlist or it gets denied.\n\nActually no - if `ask` is `off` and the command isn't in the allowlist, it should either:\n1. Auto-approve and run\n2. Deny with \"allowlist miss\"\n\nIt seems like the behavior is #2 - even with `ask: \"off\"`, if the command isn't in the allowlist it gets denied. That's not what we expected based on the screenshots shown.\n\nWait, looking at the original screenshot again - the `ask: \"off\"` was in the `defaults` section and also per-agent. But the issue is that even with `ask: \"off\"`, commands that aren't in the allowlist still fail.\n\nHmm, but the user showed screenshots saying \"改了这些文件就可以不用审批了\" - implying that changing `ask: \"off\"` should bypass the need for approval. Maybe there's something different about their setup vs. our setup.\n\nActually, I think the issue might be that `ask: \"off\"` means \"don't ask for approval\" but commands still need to be in the allowlist. The \"approval\" is different from the \"allowlist\" - approval is the interactive confirmation, while allowlist is whether the command is permitted at all.\n\n\nSo the user might be confused - they thought `ask: \"off\"` would bypass everything, but actually it only bypasses the confirmation prompt. The command still needs to be in the allowlist to run at all. Though their screenshots suggested this worked for them, so maybe there's a configuration detail I'm missing about how their setup differs from ours.","thinkingSignature":"4790dae5274710fe752f3755556b952babcd3a48fea00db145235db1d99d377a"},{"type":"text","text":"奇怪，还是被拒绝了。看起来 `ask: \"off\"` 只跳过了\"是否允许\"的确认弹窗，但命令本身还是要在 allowlist 里才行的。\n\n让我加一下 echo 和 date：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6o3btwm042d7_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/halei/.openclaw/exec-approvals.json"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":9374,"output":560,"cacheRead":12632,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":22566,"cost":{"input":0.0028122,"output":0.000672,"cacheRead":0.0007579199999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.004242119999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775176654714,"responseId":"061e3ecf0845934e6336e0a9fbef4457"}}
